-- Italy, Paraguay Tied 1-1 After 63 Minutes at World Cup Match in Cape Town
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-14T19:50:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/italy-paraguay-tied-1-1-after-63-minutes-at-world-cup-match-in-cape-town.html

          
          
             Daniele De Rossi scored for
defending champion Italy to tie their opening group match
against Paraguay at soccer’s World Cup at 1-1 after 63 minutes
in Cape Town, South Africa.   
 Antolin Alcaraz had given Paraguay a halftime lead after
outjumping Fabio Cannavaro to head past goalkeeper Gianluigi
Buffon.  
 Italy, which has progressed from the group stage at the
past eight World Cups, is aiming to match Brazil’s record five
titles.  
 New Zealand and Slovakia are also in Group F.  
          
          


  


        